<title type="html"><![CDATA[Glitch help]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6907&amp;p=66813#p66813"><![CDATA[
You said you found the reason of the glitch but there is no explanation about what was the mistake.  It would be nice if you could explain what caused the fuzz.<br /><br />Second,  if I read the code properly I see that you "reset the scroll" back to X:0/Y:E8. Am I correct?  I guess what Bregalad meant by "reset the scroll" is that on every frame, you have to set back the current value of the X/Y location of the scroll since they get trashed when content of PPU is updated (the loopy register thingy).  I had this issue before and my screen was jumpy.  After setting back the value of the current scroll position, everything was fine. I didn't have to reset to 0, just set back the current value of the scroll.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3559">Banshaku</a> — Fri Aug 27, 2010 6:47 am</p><hr />
